Chamber of Healing~
   This austere chamber is dimly lit by several glowing charcoal braziers, the
faint light they cast barely penetrating the thick smoke of the chamber.
Faintly decernable through the smokey haze is a small bronze statue of
Hukulokujyu, the Buddha of long life, and before it rests a fuming bowl of
incense. Several very small, razor sharp needles are laid out on a length of
silk before the statue, the purpose of which you can only begin to guess.
~
