#21821
Chamber of Fasting~
   This chamber is very warm, and the floor is thickly padded with woven mats.
Several large charcoal braziers give off waves of pleasant heat and provide
ample light to see. This is where the monks come to meditate and fast,
sacrificing their desire for food in order to cleanse their minds and bodies,
and will sometimes stay here for days at a time. After they leave they are
quite unlikely to ever take food for granted again, as even a simple bowl of
rice is a feast after such an ordeal.
~
